## 5. Geolocation & Maps

- Browser Geolocation API on client to capture user's lat/lng on login/profile setup.
- All "nearby" queries use MongoDB `$geoNear` or `$near` with `2dsphere` index, radius passed as query param (e.g., 5km default).
- Mapbox GL JS (or Google Maps) to render business pins, activity pins, and event locations on a map view.
- Reverse geocoding (Mapbox Geocoding API) to convert coordinates to readable address for display.

---

## 6. Image Uploads (Cloudinary)

- `multer` + `multer-storage-cloudinary` on backend for direct-to-Cloudinary upload.
- Separate upload presets/folders: `locora/businesses`, `locora/events`, `locora/lostfound`, `locora/avatars`.
- Client-side image compression before upload (e.g., `browser-image-compression`) to keep payloads small.

---

## 7. Notifications & PWA

- In-app notifications stored in `Notification` collection, pushed live via Socket.io `new_notification` event.
- Web Push API + service worker for background push notifications (works even when app is closed) — requires VAPID keys.
- PWA setup: `vite-plugin-pwa`, `manifest.json` (name, icons, theme color), service worker caching strategy (`NetworkFirst` for API calls, `CacheFirst` for static assets).
- Installable on mobile home screen.

---

## 8. Reputation & Badge System (rule-based, no ML)

Point rules (example):
- +5 for a review that gets 3+ helpful votes
- +10 for hosting a completed activity
- +10 for hosting a completed event
- +3 for a resolved lost & found post
- +2 for joining an activity

Badge tiers: Newcomer (0-20), Active Neighbor (21-75), Community Pillar (76-200), Local Legend (200+).
Implement as a utility function `awardPoints(userId, points, reason)` called from relevant controllers, recalculates badge on threshold cross.

